 <strong>0412 168 199</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Anna-Mai Hoek (Remedial Massage) <strong>0410 214 459</strong></li>\r\n</ul>','Moved','','inherit','open','open','','387-revision-13','','','2011-12-04 21:40:57','2011-12-04 11:40:57','',387,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/387-revision-13',0,'revision','',0),(396,1,'2009-10-17 19:54:47','2009-10-17 09:54:47','<strong>Dynamic Body Therapy has an experienced team of professional therapists dedicated to excellence in health care and wellbeing. Â All of our practitioners are trained to the highest standards and registered with the required professional body governing their practice. We offer a broad range of therapies including Osteopathy, Kinesiology, Remedial Massage, Naturopathy, Acupuncture and Traditional Chinese Medicine.\r\n\r\n</strong>','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','235-revision-3','','','2009-10-17 19:54:47','2009-10-17 09:54:47','',235,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/235-revision-3',0,'revision','',0),(397,1,'2011-12-04 21:10:24','2011-12-04 11:10:24','<strong>Dynamic Body Therapy has an experienced team of professional therapists dedicated to excellence in health care and wellbeing. Â All of our practitioners are trained to the highest standards and registered with the required professional body governing their practice. We offer a range of therapies including Osteopathy, Kinesiology, Remedial Massage.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','235-revision-4','','','2011-12-04 21:10:24','2011-12-04 11:10:24','',235,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/235-revision-4',0,'revision','',0),(398,1,'2011-03-07 08:58:11','2011-03-06 22:58:11','Dr Shari Trimble\r\nRegistered Osteopath, Biodynamic Craniosacral Osteopath, Prescriptive Exercise Consultant\r\nM.H.Sc. [Osteo], B.Sc [Clin], Member of the A.O.A\r\n\r\nMONDAY 1pm - 7pm\r\nWEDNESDAY 2pm - 7pm\r\nFRIDAY 1pm - 6pm\r\n\r\nShari is the co owner of the practice with Camille de Niese. She has worked in the health and manual medicine field for more than 15 years and also lectures in anatomy, pathology and clinical skills.\r\n\r\nShariâ€™s passion is to assist in helping the body\'s own wisdom restore health and balance. With a nurturing and gentle style, Shari tailors her treatments to each individual, working to stimulate the body\'s natural ability to heal itself.\r\n<h3><strong>Special Interest in Yoga and Performance Arts</strong></h3>\r\nWith her past experience in engineering, a Bachelor degree in Clinical Science and a Masters in Osteopathy, Shari has a thorough understanding of body mechanics and a unique capacity to view your injury in the context of activity and training. Shari focuses on helping you to rehabilitate your injury whilst continuing to practice and train, and how to avoid further disruption to your program.\r\n\r\nCurrently a member of the Footscray Womenâ€™s Circus Shari also runs her dogs and practices yoga daily. She has a background in dance, pilates and long distance running and has completed postgraduate studies in exercise prescription &amp; clinical pilates.\r\n<h3><strong>Special Interests in Womenâ€™s Health, Fertility &amp; Children</strong></h3>\r\nShari has completed post graduate osteopathic studies in obstetrics &amp; gynaecology and the treatment of children and enjoys working with the challenges women may face during pregnancy and motherhood.\r\n<h3><strong><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-255\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/pregnancy.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"266\" height=\"266\" />Pregnancy</strong></h3>\r\nDuring pregnancy there are many physiological processes that take place and large changes to a womenâ€™s body occur in a relatively short space of time. A hormone called Relaxin softens the ligaments around the joints of the pelvis which is a natural process and assists childbirth. However for some women this process can cause the joints of the pelvis to loosen too much and can result in the pelvis becoming unstable or out of alignment and in a susceptible women can contribute to low back and pelvic pain.\r\n\r\nPost pregnancy there will be pressure on different areas such as the upper back and neck. This may be due to poor posture during breast feeding and incorrect lifting techniques.Â  Osteopathic treatment and corrective muscle re-education can aid in the way the body copes with these pressures.\r\n<h3><strong>Babies &amp; Children</strong></h3>\r\nA baby will often communicate there is a problem by being unsettled, irritable or wakeful. Symptoms in a newborn baby to be aware of are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Colic</li>\r\n	<li>excessive wind</li>\r\n	<li>continuous crying</li>\r\n	<li>difficulty feeding or a preference to feed from one breast</li>\r\n	<li>sleeping difficulties</li>\r\n	<li>stiffness of the neck muscles</li>\r\n	<li>favouring the head to one side</li>\r\n	<li>a misshapen head</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-257\" src=\"http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/osteopathy-for-infants1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"228\" height=\"235\" />Biodynamic/Cranial Osteopathy can be useful in treating a wide range of symptoms and conditions in children including the following\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>back and neck pain</li>\r\n	<li>ear infections and glue ear</li>\r\n	<li>growing pains</li>\r\n	<li>headaches</li>\r\n	<li>behavioural problems</li>\r\n	<li>hyperactivity</li>\r\n	<li>speech problems</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nServices Offered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Read About Osteopathy\" href=\"/services/osteopathy\">Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/services/biodynamic-cranial-osteopathy\">Biodynamics/Cranial Osteopathy</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Shari Trimble','','inherit','open','open','','45-revision-28','','','2011-03-07 08:58:11','2011-03-06 22:58:11','',45,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/45-revision-28',0,'revision','',0),(376,1,'2010-02-20 18:39:31','2010-02-20 08:39:31','Dip.H.Sc. in Remedial Therapy\r\nDip. Anatomy, Physiology &amp; Massage [London]\r\nITEC Dip Massage [London]\r\nAAMT, ANTA, AKA (student member), Network Fitness\r\n\r\nWEDNESDAY 12pm - 7:15pm\r\nTHURSDAY 12pm - 7:15pm\r\nFRIDAY 12pm - 7:15pm\r\n\r\nCamille has a background in dance (ballet, contemporary &amp; African dance) and sport (netball) and understands the difficulty in overcoming injuries while still being able to keep up with ones physical and lifestyle pursuits.Â  It is this background and her own struggles with injury that lead to Camille becoming a physical therapist.\r\n\r\nCamille de Niese has been working in the field of manual therapy for 13 years and has attained qualifications and skills in remedial therapy, massage, kinesiology, manual lymphatic drainage, cupping, neurostructural integration, reiki and pilates instruction.\r\n\r\nHaving worked primarily in the structural field of therapy Camille has seen first hand the extent to which our emotions and stress levels impact on us physically causing pain, stiffness and ill health.Â  Often a purely physical approach to treatment is limited and achieving a full and lasting recovery is prolonged due to not fully resolving the primary cause of ill health.Â  This realisation resulted in Camille undertaking further study in Kinesiology which looks at our emotional, energetic, spiritual and physical health.\r\n\r\nRemedial Kinesiology is Camille\'s combination of remedial therapy and kinesiology to provide the client with a treatment that deals with the physical, emotional, energetic and spiritual blocks to good health and well being.Â  Through the use of kinesiology Camille is able to determine the priority issue to be dealt with in any given session and works toward restoring balance on all levels.\r\n\r\nCamille offers a variety of single therapy treatments including deep tissue massage, remedial therapy, lymphatic drainage and kinesiology as well as remedial kinesiology which provides a truly holistic treatment plan for those clients seeking to work towards resolving more long standing physical and emotional negative patterns, by incorporating a variety of therapies, treatment techniques and rehab exercises to resolve dysfunction at the root cause not just treat the symptoms.','Camille de Niese','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-7','','','2010-02-20 18:39:31','2010-02-20 08:39:31','',62,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/62-revision-7',0,'revision','',0),(400,1,'2011-12-04 20:59:39','2011-12-04 10:59:39','We\'ve moved! But just a short stroll around the corner at The Block Arcade, 280 Collins Street. We are on the first level in suite 109. Take lift 1 at the Collins Street entrance opposite The Hopetoun Tea Rooms to the first level, there is a small set of stairs down to a corridor where you will find us at the end. Refer to map on contact page.\r\n\r\nSome of our practitioners have also moved and can be contacted directly for new locations:\r\nDr. Chris Eddy (Chinese Medicine/Acupuncture) 0400 102 023\r\nAnne Howard (Naturopath) 0412 168 199\r\nAnna-Mai Hoek (Remedial Massage) 0410 214 459','Moved','','inherit','open','open','','387-revision-4','','','2011-12-04 20:59:39','2011-12-04 10:59:39','',387,'http://www.dynamicbodytherapy.com/uncategorized/387-revision-4',0,'revision','',0),(401,1,'2011-12-04 21:16:09','2011-12-04 11:16:09','We\'ve moved! But just a short stroll around the corner to:\r\n\r\nThe Block Arcade,\r\n\r\n280 Collins Street.\r\n\r\nWe are on the first level in suite 109. Take lift 1 at the Collins Street entrance opposite The Hopetoun Tea Rooms to the first level, there is a small set of stairs down to a corridor where you will find us at the end. Refer to map on contact page.\r\n\r\nSome of our practitioners have also moved and can be contacted directly for new locations:\r\nDr. Chris Eddy (Chinese Medicine/Acupuncture) 0400 102 023\r\nAnne Howard (Naturopath) 0412 168 199\r\nAnna-Mai Hoe